- Those situations would include any body ornamentation that interferes with the performance of the member's military duties.

- "The following factors (not all inclusive) are considered when making a determination to restrict the wear of non-visible body ornaments:
- whether it impairs the safe and effective operation of weapons, military equipment or machinery;
- does it pose a health or safety hazard to the wearer or others;
-or does it interfere with the proper wear of special or protective clothing or equipment such as helmets, flak jackets, flight duty uniforms, camouflaged uniforms, gas masks, wet suits and crash rescue equipment
